Aigent Pizza OS is a **human-friendly control interface for complex AI agent systems**.

Instead of navigating complicated dashboards or terminal commands, users interact with infrastructure through a **visual pizza-style control surface inspired by 8-bit computing architecture**.

The result is a system that makes **distributed AI understandable and controllable by humans.**

---

# 🎥 Demo

Example prototype interface:

```
🍕 Pizza Control Surface
 ├── Agents
 ├── Telemetry
 ├── Compute
 ├── Storage
 ├── Security
 ├── Monitoring
 ├── Networking
 └── Memory
```

Each slice represents a **core system module**.

The interface acts as a **navigation layer for AI infrastructure**.

---

# 🧠 The Idea

Computers think in bits.

```
1 byte = 8 bits
```

The pizza interface reflects this structure visually.

```
        Monitoring
   Security        Agents

  Storage           Compute

   Networking     Telemetry
        Memory
```

Instead of complex nested dashboards, the system presents infrastructure as **modular visual segments.**

This allows users to quickly understand and interact with complex systems.

---

# ⚙️ Architecture

Aigent Pizza OS sits on top of a distributed infrastructure stack.

```
┌──────────────────────────┐
│     Pizza Control UI     │
│   (Human Interface)      │
└───────────▲──────────────┘
            │
┌───────────┴──────────────┐
│     Agent Execution      │
│  Autonomous Task Layer   │
└───────────▲──────────────┘
            │
┌───────────┴──────────────┐
│      Telemetry Layer     │
│  System Metrics + State  │
└───────────▲──────────────┘
            │
┌───────────┴──────────────┐
│     Hardware Nodes       │
│  Pi • Mac • GPU • Edge   │
└──────────────────────────┘
```

